 <foreign xml:lang="gez">በል፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> bal </quote></cit> <gramGrp><pos expand="verbum">v.</pos> 2SgM Imper.</gramGrp> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> come on!, well then!, so then! </quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Kane1990DictAmhVol2"/><citedRange unit="page"> 1096a</citedRange></bibl>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">በሉ፡ ትፍኡ፡ ዘበላዕክሙ፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="it"><quote> Su, sputate quel che avete mangiato </quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Marrassini2003GabraManfasQeddusTextus"/><citedRange unit="page"> 86 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:Marrassini2003GabraManfasQeddusVersio"/><citedRange unit="page"> 30 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘Su <foreign xml:lang="gez">በል፡</foreign> in questo senso cf. p. es. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Marrassini1981YohannesMisrakawi"/><citedRange unit="page."> 212 and 213 n. 3</citedRange></bibl>. ’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Marrassini2003GabraManfasQeddusVersio"/><citedRange unit="page"> 30 n. 156</citedRange></bibl>); (‘Uno dei tanti esempi di bal come “orsù”, a non “di”. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Marrassini1981YohannesMisrakawi"/><citedRange unit="page"> 213 n. 3</citedRange></bibl>.’). <sense n="E" xml:id="TE"> This seems to be an Amharic expression. <foreign xml:lang="am">በል</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="am">በዪ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="am">በሉ</foreign> are very often used in spoken Amharic with the meaning ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> come on!, well then!, so then! </quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Kane1990DictAmhVol2"/><citedRange unit="page"> 1096a</citedRange></bibl>. 
